  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="ITA41">
<l>poruḷā lamarulakam pukkiyala lākā</l>
<l>taruḷā laṟamaruḷu maṉṟē – yaruḷālē</l>
<l>māmaṟaiyōrk kīnta maṇivaṇṇaṉ pātamē</l>
<l>nīmaṟavē ṉeñcē niṉai</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>By wealth, there is no entering and progressing into the immortal world.</l>
<l>By grace, isn’t Dharma also grace? The sapphire-coloured one,</l>
<l>who by grace alone gave [himself] to the great Veda expert<note xml:lang="en" place="foot">It seems best to take the plural maṟaiyōr as a honorific form and another reference to the seer Markaṇḍeya, who is called maṟaiyavaṉ in Po. 94 where the context is clearer and allows the identification.</note>, his feet</l>
<l>don’t you forget, heart, think [of them].</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
